data.description: Welcome to your dream home! Step into a world of timeless elegance with original oak wood floors throughout most of the house, exuding warmth and character. The kitchen and dining areas boast beautiful tile floors, offering both style and practicality. With the septic recently cleaned and plumbing, electrical, and HVAC systems only 6-7 years old, you'll experience peace of mind and modern convenience.    Indulge in the serenity of nature with a huge backyard and a picturesque lake as your backdrop, providing a tranquil escape from the bustle of everyday life. The 800 sqft of expandable area presents an incredible opportunity to craft your dream great room and master bedroom suite, with oversized electrical and HVAC systems ready to accommodate your vision.    Take advantage of the little workshop area in the garage, perfect for your creative projects. Rest easy knowing your home is hurricane-proof with impact windows, energy-efficient, and fully insulated in the attic, ensuring comfort and safety year-round. Situated as one of the highest houses in the neighborhood, you'll enjoy breathtaking views and a sense of prestige.    Discover your green thumb with two irrigated garden areas, complete with an avocado tree that adds a touch of natural beauty to your surroundings. Embrace relaxation and privacy with blackout curtains and blinds, allowing you to create the perfect ambiance in every room.    Unleash your inner entertainer with the possibility of a sparkling swimming pool in the expansive backyard. The front yard features an irrigation and sprinkler system, while the back yard is partially irrigated, making maintenance a breeze. Gather around the fire pit in the evenings, creating lasting memories with family and friends.    Furnishings negotiable, meaning you can seamlessly transition into your new home. And as the day winds down, prepare to be captivated by stunning sunsets right in your own backyard. Don't miss out on this incredible opportunity to experience luxury, comfort, and endless possibilities in your new home.
